    "body": "As environment wiring tends to grow over time `.env` files are easier to maintain and include in compose yaml files\r\n\r\nI'm my point of view, is better to decouple env values and use `env_file` instead of `environment` only/preferably when they are distributed across many compose defs.\r\n\r\nOther benefits:\r\n* DRY\r\n* Force .env.<context> conventions",
